defs.name: PacketErr
defs.value: PacketErr::{OverflowSize, InvalidOpCode, StrOutOfBounds, OpCodeOutOfBounds, ErrCodeOutOfBounds, Utf8Error}

defs.name: ErrorCode
defs.value: ErrorCode::{NotDefined, FileNotFound, AccessViolation, DiskFull, IllegalTFTP, UnknownID, FileExists, NoUser}

defs.name: to_packet
defs.docs:
Returns the ERROR packet with the error code and
 the default description as the error message.

defs.name: PacketData
defs.docs:
The byte representation of a packet. Because many packets can
 be smaller than the maximum packet size, it contains a length
 parameter so that the actual packet size can be determined.

defs.name: to_slice
defs.docs: Returns a byte slice that can be sent through a socket.

defs.name: DataBytes
defs.docs:
A wrapper around the data that is to be sent in a TFTP DATA packet
 so that the data can be cloned and compared for equality.

defs.name: read
defs.docs: Creates and returns a packet parsed from its byte representation.

defs.name: bytes
defs.docs: Consumes the packet and returns the packet in byte representation.

defs.name: TftpError
defs.docs:
Error defined within the TFTP spec with an usigned integer
 error code. The server should reply with an error packet
 to the given socket address when handling this error.

defs.name: NoOpenSocket
defs.docs:
Error returned when the server cannot
 find a random open UDP port within 100 tries.

defs.name: CloseConnection
defs.docs:
Error when the connection is to be closed normally
 like when a data packet is smaller than 516 bytes.
 The server should just close the connection without
 propagating up the error.

defs.name: NoneFromSocket
defs.docs:
Error when the socket receives a None value instead
 of the source address when receiving from a socket.
 This error should be ignored by the server.

defs.name: TftpError
defs.value: TftpError::{PacketError, IoError, TftpError, NoOpenSocket, CloseConnection, NoneFromSocket}

defs.name: handle_token
defs.docs:
Called for every event sent from the event loop. The event
 is a token that can either be from the server, from an open connection,
 or from a timeout timer for a connection.

defs.name: local_addr
defs.docs: Returns the socket address of the server socket.

defs.name: create_socket
defs.docs:
Creates a std::net::UdpSocket on a random open UDP port.
 The range of valid ports is from 0 to 65535 and if the function
 cannot find a open port within 100 different random ports it returns an error.

defs.name: incr_block_num
defs.docs: Increments the block number and handles wraparound to 0 instead of overflow.
